definition.value: This is an AE which is typical manifestations of systemic diseases (e. g. Graves' disease) or typical complications of diseases in the vicinity of the orbit (e. g. orbital complications from inflammatory or tumorous sinus diseases).
This is an AE which is the product of a mismatch between the axial length of the eye and its optical power, creating blurred vision.
This is an AE which is vision loss or weakness that occurs without an apparent lesion affecting the eye.
This is an AE which is the aqueous humor-filled space inside the eye between the iris and the cornea's innermost surface, the endothelium.
This is an AE which is the aqueous humor-filled space inside the eye between the iris and the cornea's innermost surface  and it has  inflammation.
This is an AE which is a rare, late complication of cataract surgery, associated with impairment of visual function.
This is an AE which is a type of refractive error due to rotational asymmetry in the eye's refractive power.
This is an AE which refers difficulty seeing in the presence of very bright light.
This is an AE which is the most common complication after cataract surgery, with an incidence of 30%.
This is an AE which is a rare benign neuroepithelial intraventricular WHO grade I lesion found in the choroid plexus.
This is an AE which is a prevalent and potentially vision-threatening complication following glaucoma surgery.
This is an AE which is an inflammation of the choroid (thin pigmented vascular coat of the eye) and retina of the eye.
This is an AE which is a closed  macular sac, having a distinct envelope and division compared with the nearby tissue.
This is an AE which is formation of the fibrous tissue in place of the normal retinal tissue on the macular area of the retina which provides the sharpest vision in the eyes.

This is an AE which is a pathological wound healing in which connective tissue replaces normal parenchymal tissue to the extent that it goes unchecked, leading to considerable tissue remodelling and the formation of permanent scar tissue such as macular fibrosis.
This is an AE which is a small break in the macula, located in the center of the eye's light-sensitive tissue called the retina.
This is an AE which occurs when fluid and protein deposits collect on or under the macula of the eye (a yellow central area of the retina) and causes it to thicken and swell (edema).

This is an AE which is a polygenic phenotypic character determined by two distinct factors: the pigmentation of the eye's iris and the frequency-dependence of the scattering of light by the turbid medium in the stroma of the iris.
This is an AE which is supposed to be different from that of macular lamellar hole (LMH) and is thought to be caused by centripetal contraction of previously present epiretinal membrane.
This is an AE which is any pathological condition of the macula, an area at the centre of the retina that is associated with highly sensitive, accurate vision.
This is an AE which is the presence of perceived flashes of light in the field of vision.
This is an AE which is a form of uveitis localized to the vitreous and peripheral retina.

label.value: eye complication associated with device AE

definition.value: This is an AE whcih is a condition of the nasal septum in which there is a collection of pus between the mucoperichondrium and septal cartilage.
This is an AE which is a neurological disorder of excessive time spent sleeping or excessive sleepiness.
This is an AE which is a large, air-filled space above and behind the nose in the middle of the face and there is a mass.
This is an AE which is a rare sinonasal tumor that mainly occurs in adults during the 5th decade.

This is an AE which is a subtype of eosinophilic chronic rhinosinusitis (CRS) characterized by type I hypersensitivity, nasal polyposis, characteristic computed tomography scan findings, eosinophilic mucus, and the presence of fungus on surgical specimens without evidence of tissue invasion.
This is an AE which is caused by one or more volatilized chemical compounds that are generally found in low concentrations that humans and animals can perceive by their sense of smell.
This is an AE which is contents found in the human nose. It is a result of drying of the normally viscous colloidal mucus.
